Compute the absolute value of a number.



```kcl
abs(@input: number): number
```

### Arguments

| Name | Type | Description | Required |
|----------|------|-------------|----------|
| `input` | [`number`](/docs/kcl-std/types/std-types-number) |  | Yes |

### Returns

[`number`](/docs/kcl-std/types/std-types-number)


### Examples

```kcl
myAngle = -120

sketch001 = startSketchOn(XZ)
  |> startProfile(at = [0, 0])
  |> line(end = [8, 0])
  |> angledLine(
    angle = abs(myAngle),
    length = 5,
  )
  |> line(end = [-5, 0])
  |> angledLine(
    angle = myAngle,
    length = 5,
  )
  |> close()

baseExtrusion = extrude(sketch001, length = 5)
```
